               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the name of the scribe; a few groups of lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of Text I; the incipit and number of the miracles; the incipit of sections of miracles 34 and 48; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles 1-31 are numbered. The miracles (10) on fols. 8<ref type="mss" corresp="ES1ra118">1ra-118</ref>vb are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>The first miracle (fols. 9vb l.9-11va l.5) is incorporated into Text I-1, introduced with the word kǝfl “part”, and numbered as miracle 1.</note>
                     <note>On fols. 57ra-73vb, 77rb-81ra the miracles are introduced with the word kǝfl “part” and they are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>The miracle on fols. 73vb-77rb is introduced with the word mǝʿraf “chapter” and it is not numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="3r"/>Fol. 3r l.1-10: በስመ፡”…ንዌጥን፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ወአምላክነ፡ ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ በ፸፻ወ፪፻፴፡ ወአሚሩ፡ ዓመተ፡ ዓለም፡ በዘመነ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ አመ፡ ፳ወ፭፡ ለመስከረም፡ በሠረቀ፡ ሌሊት፡ ወ፬፡ በሠረቀ፡ መዓልት፡ በዕለተ፡ ዓርብ፡ በ፲ [fol. 3rb] ቱ፡ ዓመቱ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሠ፡ ነገሥት፡ ጊጋር፡ ዘተሰምየ፡ በጸጋ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሣህሉ፡ ወምሕረቱ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ወአምላክነ፡ ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወስእለተ፡ እሙ፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ገብሩ ወምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን:: <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The colophon is placed before the beginning of the text.&#xD;
According to the colophon the scribe, Gäbrä Maryam (hand a), began to write the Ms. in 7230 year of the world (= 1830 A.D.), in the year of Luke the Evangelist, on 25 of Mäskäräm, on Friday, in the 10th year of the reign of King of Kings Gigar (r. 1821-26, 1826-30, s. EAE vol. 2, p. 792). The blank for the name of a commissioner has been left unfilled.</note>
                     </colophon>
