                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Hand a: fine and careful; hand b: mediocre</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Gäbrä Maryam</persName>According to the colophon, the scribe who produced the Ms. is Gäbrä Maryam (hand a). His name is also mentioned in the supplication formulas up to fol. 53va.<date>First half of the 19th century</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: fols. 3ra-79ra l.7: the letters are slightly right-sloping, tall and slim. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
In fols. 59ra-79ra the handwriting slightly changes: the letters are bigger in size, occasionally broadly spaced (fols. 71r, 74v). <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
Hand b: fols. 79ra l.5-118vb: the letters are right-sloping, wide and angular, the individual strokes forming the letter are frequently not joined.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
